You shouldn&#39;t need the _SerializedName_ _annotations_.\
These are for when the _keys_ are not valid _Java_ variable names, e.g. _&quot;abc-123&quot;_, or _&quot;123abc&quot;_.

Here is an example.

```java
class Example {
    String key1;
    int key2;
}
```

```java
String s = &quot;{ \&quot;key1\&quot;: \&quot;abc\&quot;, \&quot;key2\&quot;: 1 }&quot;;
Gson g = new Gson();
Example e = g.fromJson(s, Example.class);
```

