Questions:

1. Is it possible to convert `dataSentToConsumer` to `bytesSentByProducer`?

2. If yes, how can I fix this issue if the only part under my control is the consumer? How can I undo the UTF-8 encoding which happens inside the misconfigured Kafka cluster?

Note: The obvious solution is to configure the Kafka cluster properly. The same consumer works fine in another environment where there is a normal Kafka cluster which doesn&#39;t do any strange transformation. This obvious and easiest solution is not available for bureaucratic reasons.



